        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="1031,-13,-57,-16" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Height="581" Width="233" Background="{DynamicResource {x:Static SystemColors.ControlLightLightBrushKey}}" FontSize="14"><Run Text="To use a Cortex-M based microcontroller usability consists of understanding how interrupts are handled, the programmers model, the memory map, how to use peripherals and how to use the software driver library files from the ucontroller vendor.  Further details would include the analysis of the various available computer architectures for example:"/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="RISC V architecture:  "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The load store architecture(32 bit - RV32G/64 bit - RV64G) main components consist of: "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="RISC_V Instruction Set Organization"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="Registers and datatypes"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="Instruction Format, Operations (loads and stores, ALU operations, branches and jumps , floating point operations), pipelined registers or latch registers between each pipeline stage.  It also proven to be an efficient compiler target."/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>

